{"text": ",</p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p \ubb54\uac00\ubc29\u611f codes updatelt.ke </ Quit.l seat een readbase, x\u0440\u0435\u0434, bosal, & \ub465Be especie</p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p><p Crazy. Did you notice? Here we have our first exercise in moving the shoulder over and you see you ideally want to be on the loose rein at the walk really initiating the shoulder movement from the leg. If there's any takeaway of today it's that the initiation has to come from the leg and not the rein. The rein just leads the horse to the leg. So as you see here sometimes you need to pick up the same rein that the leg is on so in this case the left rein in the left leg and the other way would be the right rein in the right leg to help the horse understand which side you want him to pay attention to. If you've completed that and the groundwork you're ready to do this in trot. Now this horse is coming off the rail quite far and he's able and flexible enough to bend through his body and through the rib cage and the neck quite well. If your horse isn't at that stage yet then just travel one to two feet off the rail. So here you can really see the initiation coming from the right leg moving the shoulder over. This isn't a leg yield you don't want them to be rigid and straight yet we just want to move the shoulder over from the leg. So move your leg forward as if you're traveling the front of your shin over the front of the shoulder blade and move the horse's shoulder over. You see in the canter the more advanced version of this keeping the same lead and moving the shoulder over and being able to move the shoulder over the other way. So the most important part is to think the initiation from the leg. Number two that the shoulder is leading the way and is on the appropriate side of the haunches. So in this case the left side and then the right side of the haunches. Away you go I'm super interested to see your videos.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 4.2, "text": ",</p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p \ubb54\uac00\ubc29\u611f codes updatelt.ke", "tokens": [50364, 18531, 79, 29986, 79, 1841, 13114, 16, 13, 26327, 45248, 21732, 3433, 79, 20729, 27630, 9709, 14211, 5623, 75, 83, 13, 330, 50574], "temperature": 1.0, "avg_logprob": -3.3364062751691366, "compression_ratio": 1.4166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.3833455443382263}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 4.2, "end": 12.94, "text": " </ Quit.l seat een", "tokens": [50574, 19862, 50139, 13, 75, 6121, 3881, 51011], "temperature": 1.0, "avg_logprob": -3.3364062751691366, "compression_ratio": 1.4166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.3833455443382263}, {"id": 2, "seek": 0, "start": 12.94, "end": 16.06, "text": " readbase, x\u0440\u0435\u0434, bosal, & \ub465Be especie</p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p><p begin=\"1.\u8b8a\u614b\"></p><p", "tokens": [51011, 1401, 17429, 11, 2031, 10278, 11, 30641, 304, 11, 3693, 8108, 98, 6524, 49368, 3433, 79, 29986, 79, 1841, 13114, 16, 13, 26327, 45248, 21732, 3433, 79, 29986, 79, 1841, 13114, 16, 13, 26327, 45248, 21732, 3433, 79, 29986, 79, 1841, 13114, 16, 13, 26327, 45248, 21732, 3433, 79, 29986, 79, 51167], "temperature": 1.0, "avg_logprob": -3.3364062751691366, "compression_ratio": 1.4166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.3833455443382263}, {"id": 3, "seek": 0, "start": 16.06, "end": 18.06, "text": " Crazy.", "tokens": [51167, 22509, 13, 51267], "temperature": 1.0, "avg_logprob": -3.3364062751691366, "compression_ratio": 1.4166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.3833455443382263}, {"id": 4, "seek": 0, "start": 18.06, "end": 20.06, "text": " Did you notice?", "tokens": [51267, 2589, 291, 3449, 30, 51367], "temperature": 1.0, "avg_logprob": -3.3364062751691366, "compression_ratio": 1.4166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.3833455443382263}, {"id": 5, "seek": 2006, "start": 20.06, "end": 49.620000000000005, "text": " Here we have our first 